1
00:02:17,284 --> 00:02:18,484
SPRING

2
00:02:50,724 --> 00:02:52,564
Sus, get up.

3
00:02:54,244 --> 00:02:56,284
Good morning, darling.

4
00:03:00,124 --> 00:03:01,444
Get up, darling.

5
00:03:03,004 --> 00:03:04,484
FOR MUM

6
00:03:11,884 --> 00:03:12,884
Here.

7
00:03:21,244 --> 00:03:23,124
Good morning. - Hi.

8
00:03:25,484 --> 00:03:27,724
Why did you sleep in the same bed?

9
00:03:27,724 --> 00:03:29,364
Susana was having nightmares.

10
00:03:30,444 --> 00:03:31,484
Done.

11
00:03:33,964 --> 00:03:35,684
Wash your face, Susan.

12
00:03:35,684 --> 00:03:37,444
Oh man.

13
00:03:43,004 --> 00:03:44,644
Go wake your sister up.

14
00:03:59,684 --> 00:04:01,364
Hey! - Stop daydreaming!

15
00:04:01,364 --> 00:04:02,804
I gotta work. - Get in.

16
00:04:02,804 --> 00:04:04,644
I'll walk. - I'll drive you.

17
00:04:07,324 --> 00:04:09,444
How you doing? - Good. You?

18
00:04:10,484 --> 00:04:12,124
Hamdulillah.

19
00:04:12,124 --> 00:04:15,204
Where are the girls? - At school, where else?

20
00:04:15,684 --> 00:04:17,604
You're looking good. - Thanks.

21
00:04:17,604 --> 00:04:20,324
New watch? - No, it's really old.

22
00:04:20,324 --> 00:04:23,164
Eyes on the road! - I just haven't worn it for ages.

23
00:04:23,164 --> 00:04:26,364
From Murti? - Of course! What do you think?

24
00:04:26,364 --> 00:04:28,204
He's a good man, Murti.

25
00:04:28,204 --> 00:04:32,324
He treats you like a queen. - Typical Arab man.

26
00:04:32,324 --> 00:04:34,644
It's nice. - Yeah, alhamdulillah.

27
00:04:35,444 --> 00:04:36,684
Hamdulillah.

28
00:04:39,244 --> 00:04:41,444
No, the one before Real City...

29
00:04:42,124 --> 00:04:43,724
This one? - Yeah, that one.

30
00:04:43,724 --> 00:04:45,724
You like it, huh? - Turn it up!

31
00:04:47,004 --> 00:04:48,284
Drive Sadah!

32
00:05:02,444 --> 00:05:04,564
Good morning.

33
00:05:04,564 --> 00:05:07,044
Sorry I'm late. My colleague is off sick.

34
00:05:07,044 --> 00:05:08,884
Amir, hi. - Hello.

35
00:05:10,164 --> 00:05:12,044
That's the one.

36
00:05:12,044 --> 00:05:13,444
You need to...

37
00:05:14,164 --> 00:05:16,284
sign here, please. - Yep.

38
00:05:19,004 --> 00:05:20,084
Perfect.

39
00:05:20,084 --> 00:05:22,964
Here, the fee exemption form.

40
00:05:27,564 --> 00:05:29,164
Are they your girls?

41
00:05:29,164 --> 00:05:30,844
The girls on the photo. - Yes.

42
00:05:30,844 --> 00:05:31,924
Really?

43
00:05:32,364 --> 00:05:34,564
Wow, they're adorable. - Thank you.

44
00:05:34,564 --> 00:05:38,244
They really look like you. I can see you in all of them.

45
00:05:38,844 --> 00:05:41,324
Right, I'm going to photocopy this.

46
00:05:41,324 --> 00:05:43,884
We don't need this, it's the old one. - OK.

47
00:05:43,884 --> 00:05:49,244
My friends play some traditional music... - OK.

48
00:05:49,244 --> 00:05:51,324
They play the oud... - Nice.

49
00:05:51,324 --> 00:05:52,724
Do you play too?

50
00:05:52,724 --> 00:05:56,084
I play the flute, but I haven't played for ages.

51
00:05:56,964 --> 00:06:01,844
I thought you might like to come to the party with me.

52
00:06:01,844 --> 00:06:05,724
We could have a drink and watch the concert together.

53
00:06:07,404 --> 00:06:09,604
I don't have the time, Khaled. Sorry.

54
00:06:11,004 --> 00:06:13,324
"No time. Sorry." - No time.

55
00:08:40,363 --> 00:08:44,164
Good morning, Maryam. - Morning, Abu Jamal. How's it going?

56
00:08:44,164 --> 00:08:45,164
Hamdulillah.

57
00:08:50,884 --> 00:08:53,644
Have you booked the flights? - Yep.

58
00:08:53,644 --> 00:08:56,804
It's still warm. - Grab the garlic sauce.

59
00:08:56,804 --> 00:08:59,124
When is your flight? - Thursday.

60
00:08:59,124 --> 00:09:00,964
That's not so bad, is it?

61
00:09:00,964 --> 00:09:04,084
No, but I've gotso much to do before then.

62
00:09:04,084 --> 00:09:09,284
Buying presents? - Yeah. Presents, and loads of paperwork.

63
00:09:09,884 --> 00:09:12,364
Be happy you get to see the sun!

64
00:09:12,364 --> 00:09:15,884
I am, it's just the difficult circumstances.

65
00:09:15,884 --> 00:09:18,804
Let me know if you need any help. - Sure.

66
00:09:18,804 --> 00:09:23,884
Seriously. Don't hesitate. - Yeah, I'll see what I get done.

67
00:09:23,884 --> 00:09:25,244
I'll take care of everything.

68
00:09:29,164 --> 00:09:30,684
Open sesame.

69
00:09:31,404 --> 00:09:34,444
Are the boarding passes on your phone? - Oh...

70
00:09:35,244 --> 00:09:36,604
Have a good journey.

71
00:09:36,604 --> 00:09:38,644
Thank you, thank you.

72
00:09:38,644 --> 00:09:42,084
Say hi to all the family from me. - Will do.

73
00:09:42,084 --> 00:09:43,764
And kiss Beirut for me!

74
00:09:43,764 --> 00:09:46,724
Have a last look at your car while it's still nice.

75
00:09:46,724 --> 00:09:49,244
Oh, you'll be fine.

76
00:09:49,244 --> 00:09:51,644
And the parcel for Jibril. - Yep.

77
00:09:51,644 --> 00:09:55,644
I registered your visit. Don't forget to take your ID.

78
00:09:55,644 --> 00:09:58,044
Alright. See you.

79
00:09:58,044 --> 00:09:59,084
Bye.

80
00:10:11,044 --> 00:10:13,084
What's the point?

81
00:11:25,724 --> 00:11:26,724
Hi.

82
00:11:28,324 --> 00:11:29,764
Maryam.

83
00:11:29,764 --> 00:11:30,844
I know.

84
00:11:32,684 --> 00:11:34,524
We've seen each other before.

85
00:11:35,684 --> 00:11:37,444
At the wedding.

86
00:11:38,124 --> 00:11:40,804
It was a while ago, you were wearing a blue dress.

87
00:11:40,804 --> 00:11:41,804
Yep.

88
00:11:46,564 --> 00:11:49,604
I handed in your parcel from Sadah. - Thanks.

89
00:11:49,604 --> 00:11:52,044
She's really sorry. - It's fine.

90
00:11:52,484 --> 00:11:56,124
Did Murti fly over with her to Beirut? - Yeah, it's his uncle.

91
00:12:08,204 --> 00:12:10,324
It's crazy getting in here.

92
00:12:12,564 --> 00:12:15,124
Getting out's even crazier.

93
00:12:26,044 --> 00:12:28,164
What do you do in here all day?

94
00:12:34,124 --> 00:12:35,484
Sit around.

95
00:12:37,004 --> 00:12:38,484
Read.

96
00:12:39,004 --> 00:12:40,404
Exercise.

97
00:12:41,604 --> 00:12:44,484
I'm doing an apprenticeship as a locksmith.

98
00:12:44,484 --> 00:12:46,564
Learning to break into places?

99
00:12:49,324 --> 00:12:52,124
I'm also in this group with a priest.

100
00:12:52,124 --> 00:12:54,044
Or pastor... no, he's a priest.

101
00:12:54,964 --> 00:12:55,964
Sorry.

102
00:13:00,484 --> 00:13:03,164
He's the only person who understands what's going on here.

103
00:13:06,044 --> 00:13:09,844
I'm trying to do my A-levels, and he's helping me with that.

104
00:13:09,844 --> 00:13:11,764
A-levels? - Yeah.

105
00:13:11,764 --> 00:13:12,884
Cool.

106
00:13:13,844 --> 00:13:14,964
Jibril.

107
00:13:16,724 --> 00:13:18,204
Jibril...

108
00:13:18,204 --> 00:13:20,084
It's a nice name.

109
00:13:20,084 --> 00:13:22,044
It's nice the way you say it.

110
00:13:22,884 --> 00:13:25,724
Don't you speak Arabic? - Only a little bit.

111
00:13:31,244 --> 00:13:34,084
My dad didn't really want us to...

112
00:13:35,764 --> 00:13:37,644
speak Arabic.

113
00:13:37,644 --> 00:13:40,484
He wanted us to speak German, so we felt like we belonged.

114
00:13:40,484 --> 00:13:42,244
I can speak both.

115
00:13:43,564 --> 00:13:45,364
That's you.

116
00:13:46,484 --> 00:13:48,524
But... I can still learn it.

117
00:13:51,804 --> 00:13:54,484
I brought you some chocolate. - Thanks.

118
00:13:55,324 --> 00:13:57,324
I was hoping it was for me.

119
00:14:12,484 --> 00:14:14,404
I have to get going.

120
00:14:14,404 --> 00:14:16,524
Are you gonna come again?

121
00:14:17,284 --> 00:14:19,284
It was an honour, Jibril.

122
00:14:29,684 --> 00:14:30,684
Thanks.

123
00:14:32,084 --> 00:14:35,804
When one door closes, the other will open.

124
00:14:35,804 --> 00:14:37,524
Have a nice day. Thanks. You too.

125
00:14:39,724 --> 00:14:41,604
Have a nice day. - Bye.

126
00:15:14,324 --> 00:15:16,364
Shall I...? - We're about to eat.

127
00:15:16,364 --> 00:15:18,644
But not the yellow stuff! - Right.

128
00:15:18,644 --> 00:15:20,884
What do you want? - Rice.

129
00:15:21,764 --> 00:15:24,204
Do you want the rest?

130
00:15:24,204 --> 00:15:25,284
No?

131
00:15:25,284 --> 00:15:26,444
Not that much!

132
00:15:27,004 --> 00:15:29,004
Not so much. - Stop!

133
00:15:29,004 --> 00:15:30,564
That's enough.

134
00:15:33,364 --> 00:15:35,284
Peppers too, Elin?

135
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:38,724
How was your day?

136
00:15:38,724 --> 00:15:41,164
What did you do? - Nothing special.

137
00:15:42,244 --> 00:15:44,204
How was your day at Dad's?

138
00:15:44,204 --> 00:15:45,484
Chilled.

139
00:15:46,524 --> 00:15:48,684
So you watched TV all day? - No.

140
00:15:48,684 --> 00:15:51,324
What did you do then? - We went out.

141
00:15:51,844 --> 00:15:54,044
We played... - Then what?

142
00:15:54,044 --> 00:15:56,164
I told you, we went out.

143
00:15:56,164 --> 00:15:57,764
You had a good time then?

144
00:16:03,324 --> 00:16:05,684
Did you clean for him after that?

145
00:16:05,684 --> 00:16:06,884
No!

146
00:16:09,684 --> 00:16:12,004
Seriously, Sus. Don't lie to me.

147
00:16:12,644 --> 00:16:14,844
Stop fighting all the time. - We're not.

148
00:16:14,844 --> 00:16:17,724
Just tell me. I want to know what you did. - No.

149
00:16:17,724 --> 00:16:19,724
You're my daughter. - So?

150
00:16:19,724 --> 00:16:22,044
Are you my daughter? Yes or no.

151
00:16:22,044 --> 00:16:24,204
And my father is my father.

152
00:16:25,244 --> 00:16:28,844
I don't want you vacuuming for him. - What's it to you?

153
00:16:28,844 --> 00:16:31,764
I wanna know what you've been doing. Sus! - Man!

154
00:16:34,204 --> 00:16:36,044
Give me that. - Can't I keep it?

155
00:16:36,044 --> 00:16:37,764
No, give it to me, please.

156
00:16:46,084 --> 00:16:48,204
Want a cup of tea or something?

157
00:16:48,204 --> 00:16:50,364
I could make some peppermint tea.

158
00:16:51,764 --> 00:16:53,604
I'll go upstairs in a bit.

159
00:16:56,364 --> 00:17:00,044
She said she'd call tonight. - It's already 9:15.

160
00:17:00,044 --> 00:17:01,724
She won't call anyway.

161
00:17:01,724 --> 00:17:04,764
I can't imagine my daughters not talking to me...

162
00:17:05,004 --> 00:17:06,604
Do a better job than me then.

163
00:17:07,563 --> 00:17:11,444
You can see what she's like when she gets back from her Dad's.

164
00:17:11,444 --> 00:17:13,283
She's close to him.

165
00:17:14,043 --> 00:17:15,684
That's just how it is.

166
00:17:17,444 --> 00:17:20,563
Girls are always close to their dads.

167
00:17:20,563 --> 00:17:22,684
Mine is the same. That's the way it is.

168
00:17:31,324 --> 00:17:32,804
SUMMER

169
00:17:32,804 --> 00:17:34,364
Morning check!

170
00:18:31,444 --> 00:18:33,084
Say something.

171
00:18:33,564 --> 00:18:35,684
How's your Arabic coming along?

172
00:18:37,444 --> 00:18:39,004
Not great.

173
00:18:39,004 --> 00:18:41,604
Did you even start? - Not really.

174
00:18:41,604 --> 00:18:43,644
You can't be bothered?

175
00:18:44,644 --> 00:18:46,604
How are your kids?

176
00:18:46,604 --> 00:18:49,404
Susana's giving me a tough time, but they're good.

177
00:18:49,404 --> 00:18:51,404
Yara's Arabic is really good.

178
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:53,324
Really? - Yep.

179
00:18:53,324 --> 00:18:55,844
And Susana? - She can't be bothered.

180
00:18:56,124 --> 00:18:58,604
She's more into her private life. - The old one?

181
00:18:59,404 --> 00:19:02,164
Susana's the oldest one, Yara's the middle one.

182
00:19:02,164 --> 00:19:04,484
Twelve. - Susana's twelve, yep.

183
00:19:05,084 --> 00:19:06,444
Pretty old.

184
00:20:01,444 --> 00:20:03,524
The coffee should be over there.

185
00:20:15,044 --> 00:20:17,444
Mr Martin, is the coffee on? - Yep.

186
00:20:17,444 --> 00:20:19,644
Let's get started then.

187
00:20:19,644 --> 00:20:22,484
It's nice to see you all here once again.

188
00:20:22,484 --> 00:20:25,764
Let us give thanks for the companionship,

189
00:20:25,764 --> 00:20:29,404
and for what we talk about, think about and feel.

190
00:20:30,084 --> 00:20:33,364
May the Lord be with us. Amen. - Amen.

191
00:20:33,804 --> 00:20:36,164
I just got this article.

192
00:20:36,164 --> 00:20:39,884
We talked about relationships in our last two sessions,

193
00:20:39,884 --> 00:20:42,564
and about our desires,

194
00:20:44,164 --> 00:20:46,684
and Mr Martin, you found something interesting.

195
00:20:48,084 --> 00:20:52,764
So, Mr Martin, do you think relationships stand a chance in prison?

196
00:20:52,764 --> 00:20:56,324
Yes and no. Maybe a tiny percentage of them work out.

197
00:20:57,444 --> 00:21:00,804
But generally, speaking from personal experience,

198
00:21:00,804 --> 00:21:02,204
no.

199
00:21:03,284 --> 00:21:06,444
Do you have a girlfriend, Mr BÃ¶hm? - Not anymore.

200
00:21:06,444 --> 00:21:08,764
It lasted for a year.

201
00:21:08,764 --> 00:21:11,524
Then we split upafter I got put in prison.

202
00:21:12,444 --> 00:21:15,404
Did you split up by mutual consent?

203
00:21:15,644 --> 00:21:17,244
Yes, we...

204
00:21:17,244 --> 00:21:19,444
She came here for a long-term visit,

205
00:21:19,444 --> 00:21:24,124
but we decided a two-hour visit once a month wasn't enough.

206
00:21:24,124 --> 00:21:27,404
Imagine seeing your wife only two hours a month.

207
00:21:27,404 --> 00:21:30,124
So we said we'd take a break for the time being.

208
00:21:30,724 --> 00:21:33,884
And what happens when I'm out is another story.

209
00:21:40,004 --> 00:21:41,844
Your cornflakes are ready.

210
00:21:41,844 --> 00:21:44,444
Mum's eating your cornflakes! - So?

211
00:21:46,124 --> 00:21:47,724
Cornflakes thief!

212
00:21:49,164 --> 00:21:50,764
Good morning.

213
00:21:51,884 --> 00:21:54,124
How's it going? Did you sleep well?

214
00:21:54,404 --> 00:21:56,164
We're having breakfast.

215
00:21:56,964 --> 00:21:58,164
Cornflakes.

216
00:21:58,164 --> 00:22:00,484
Wanna speak to him? - I do!

217
00:22:01,604 --> 00:22:03,484
Susan.

218
00:22:03,484 --> 00:22:05,084
I'm Jibril.

219
00:22:06,164 --> 00:22:08,524
I guess your Mum told you about me.

220
00:22:10,284 --> 00:22:15,244
Good. Yeah, put her on. - OK.

221
00:22:16,604 --> 00:22:17,604
Hello.

222
00:22:18,564 --> 00:22:19,884
Hello.

223
00:22:20,764 --> 00:22:22,244
Yara.

224
00:22:22,244 --> 00:22:24,404
Yara! With an "R".

225
00:22:26,604 --> 00:22:28,844
With an "R"! Yara.

226
00:22:31,164 --> 00:22:33,084
Give me the phone!

227
00:22:38,284 --> 00:22:40,084
See you sometime soon.

228
00:22:41,444 --> 00:22:43,124
You too? - Yeah.

229
00:22:43,124 --> 00:22:45,284
Here. - Good morning.

230
00:22:53,804 --> 00:22:55,324
"Good morning!"

231
00:22:59,884 --> 00:23:02,364
Hello? I'm Elin.

232
00:23:03,524 --> 00:23:05,244
Give it to me.

233
00:23:09,564 --> 00:23:11,124
They're sweet.

234
00:23:13,604 --> 00:23:15,524
They're laughing at me.

235
00:23:20,644 --> 00:23:21,644
Bye.

236
00:23:35,844 --> 00:23:37,764
No, thanks.

237
00:23:37,764 --> 00:23:41,084
Just try it, a few vitamins will do you good.

238
00:23:44,444 --> 00:23:45,564
Yummy.

239
00:23:46,884 --> 00:23:49,124
They're really nice. - Yep.

240
00:23:50,204 --> 00:23:52,244
I like them too.

241
00:23:52,804 --> 00:23:55,604
Where'd you get them? - Downstairs.

242
00:23:58,004 --> 00:24:00,564
Have you heard from your cousin?

243
00:24:00,564 --> 00:24:01,804
Samira? - Yeah.

244
00:24:02,484 --> 00:24:04,284
She's marrying some loser.

245
00:24:05,084 --> 00:24:07,644
He's got no job, nothing...

246
00:24:07,644 --> 00:24:11,884
I'm sure she knows what she's doing. - What's that supposed to mean?

247
00:24:11,884 --> 00:24:14,804
He's a waster.

248
00:24:14,804 --> 00:24:17,604
How can she marry someone who's such a failure?

249
00:24:20,244 --> 00:24:23,244
If she's happy, she's happy. - "Happy", what does that mean?

250
00:24:23,244 --> 00:24:25,444
Mum, she's in love.

251
00:24:25,444 --> 00:24:29,244
Love blossoms over time, my child.

252
00:24:29,244 --> 00:24:35,044
It's not something that's just there.

253
00:24:35,044 --> 00:24:38,204
A man needs to be able to provide for his family.

254
00:24:40,284 --> 00:24:42,284
But she has a job.

255
00:24:42,284 --> 00:24:45,244
Does she have to work to provide for him then?

256
00:24:47,284 --> 00:24:48,844
But she loves him.

257
00:24:49,764 --> 00:24:51,724
And that's enough, is it?

258
00:24:52,484 --> 00:24:55,244
Sometimes it is. - Well, it's not.

259
00:24:55,964 --> 00:24:58,284
You can fall in love very quickly,

260
00:24:58,284 --> 00:25:02,964
but true love grows and stays with you, like me and your father...

261
00:25:02,964 --> 00:25:05,844
he loved and respected me, we got through a lot together.

262
00:25:05,844 --> 00:25:08,284
God bless him. - God bless him.

263
00:25:47,244 --> 00:25:49,044
No ice cream!

264
00:25:49,484 --> 00:25:51,444
You're back already?

265
00:25:51,444 --> 00:25:53,644
I thought you were at work.

266
00:25:53,644 --> 00:25:55,764
Oh God, what are you wearing?

267
00:25:56,884 --> 00:25:59,084
Are you serious? - Yeah...

268
00:25:59,564 --> 00:26:01,604
